{"ts":"2026-06-07T10:04:51.632Z","author":"audit-platform-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-k5e8"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"pm_max_version default-BLOCK should have a per-layer warn-only toggle in settings"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"loader.ts line 907 has a `// follow-up: pm-4gw6 recommends a future settings toggle to relax this default-BLOCK to warn-only per layer.` comment. Currently pm_max_version exceeded always BLOCKS the extension (allowed: false). This is intentional for safety but creates a footgun for project-layer pinned extensions during a CLI upgrade: the extension silently stops loading until the author publishes a new version. A settings flag like `extensions.policy.pm_max_version_exceeded_mode: 'block'|'warn'` (defaulting to 'block') would let operators running managed installations opt into warn-only during upgrade windows."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Feature"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":3},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["area:extensions","compat","dx"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-07T10:04:51.632Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-07T10:04:51.632Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"audit-platform-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-ugqx"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"low"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"high"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-4gw6","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-06-07T10:04:51.632Z"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"6192d583ddf93098510c2dd35d58661dcb45e1794fbb9ae24e5e4b0b5a053bdd","message":""}
